<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Article Card</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Use for editorial content feeds — news, insights, research, and blog posts. The entire card is a link, so no separate CTA button is needed. The image draws the eye, the category chip gives instant context, the serif title creates a reading-oriented feel, and the meta footer (date + reading time) sets expectations before the user commits to clicking. Display in 2–3 column grids at desktop; single column on mobile. Avoid using this card for transactional content such as course listings or programme directories — use the Course Card variant for those instead.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview">
    <div class="ds-preview__content" style="gap: var(--sp-24); align-items: stretch;">
      <a href="#" class="card card--article" style="max-width: 340px;">
        <div class="card__image">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1523050854058-8df90110c9f1?w=680&q=80" alt="Students on campus">
        </div>
        <div class="card__body">
          <div class="card__chips">
            <span class="chip chip--green">Research</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="card__title">How Small Class Sizes Shape Graduate Outcomes</h3>
          <p class="card__desc">New longitudinal data from Regent's reveals a direct link between cohort size and first-destination employment rates across creative disciplines.</p>
          <div class="card__meta">
            <span>12 Jun 2025</span>
            <span>4 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="#" class="card card--article" style="max-width: 340px;">
        <div class="card__image">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1559136555-9303baea8ebd?w=680&q=80" alt="London cityscape">
        </div>
        <div class="card__body">
          <div class="card__chips">
            <span class="chip chip--violet">Opinion</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="card__title">Why London Remains the World's Most Valuable Classroom</h3>
          <p class="card__desc">From internship networks to cultural access, the case for studying in the capital has never been stronger.</p>
          <div class="card__meta">
            <span>3 May 2025</span>
            <span>6 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Course Card — Brand</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Use on programme directory pages and search results where each card represents a full degree or course entry. The brand-green surface signals a primary, clickable listing. The chip identifies the study level, the meta grid surfaces the three facts a prospective student needs at a glance (UCAS code, intake, duration), and the dual CTAs let users apply immediately or read more. Display in 2–3 column grids on desktop; single-column on mobile.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview ds-preview--dark">
    <div class="ds-preview__content" style="gap: var(--sp-24); align-items: stretch;">
      <div class="card card--course" style="max-width: 360px;">
        <div class="card__chips">
          <span class="chip chip--white">BA Hons</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="card__title">International Business BA (Hons)</h3>
        <p class="card__desc">Develop the skills to lead and innovate in international business with a global perspective.</p>
        <div class="card__course-meta">
          <div class="card__meta-item">
            <span class="card__meta-label">UCAS</span>
            <span class="card__meta-value">N120</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card__meta-item">
            <span class="card__meta-label">Intake</span>
            <span class="card__meta-value">September 2025</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card__meta-item">
            <span class="card__meta-label">Duration</span>
            <span class="card__meta-value">3 years full-time</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card__actions">
          <a href="#" class="btn btn--secondary-inverted btn--sm">View Course Details</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Course Card — Light</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Use the light sub-variant when the Course Card appears on a white or off-white page background where a solid brand-green card would be too heavy. The white surface keeps the card legible without losing the structured metadata layout. A coloured chip (green for undergraduate, violet for postgraduate, etc.) provides the degree-level signal. Use consistently within a grid — do not mix Brand and Light variants in the same card row.</p>
