<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Related Course Card — Light</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Use the light sub-variant when Related Course Cards appear on a white or off-white surface — for example, within an article body, a sidebar recommendation panel, or any section where a dark card would dominate the surrounding content. The coloured chip carries the degree-level signal in place of the inverted text. Keep the chip colour consistent across all cards in the same group (e.g. all green for undergraduate, all violet for postgraduate) so users can scan by level instantly.</p>
